---
<section id="about-me" class="section">
    <h2 class="section-title">About Me</h2>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="about-content">
            <div class="about-photo-container">
                <dotlottie-player 
                    src="https://lottie.host/e9bb1186-c7f4-4181-8a73-bdff02f8440c/WCRkGPlthD.lottie" 
                    background="transparent" 
                    speed="1" 
                    loop 
                    autoplay>
                </dotlottie-player>
                <img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/dqbxkmkph/image/upload/v1759879976/ANaM_ynwj0v.png" alt="Ana Maria Posada">
            </div>
            <div class="text-left">
                <h2 class="text-5xl font-bold mb-4">Meet Ana Maria</h2>
                <p class="mb-6 leading-relaxed text-lg">
                    <strong>Ani as her friends call her</strong> is a <strong>multidisciplinary designer</strong> with the soul of a musician and the heart of an artist. Currently based in Vancouver, Canada, she originally hails from Colombia, where her artistic roots were nurtured. She holds a bachelor's degree in <strong>Social Communication and Journalism</strong>, a diploma in Digital Design, and has spent years immersed in music studies.
                    </p>

                <p class="mb-6 leading-relaxed text-lg">
                Her professional path has led her to collaborate with creative agencies like <strong>Rethink</strong>, <strong>123W</strong>, and <strong>QuickFrame</strong>, as well as global brands such as <strong>IBM</strong> and <strong>Science World</strong>. This journey eventually took her to <strong>Electronic Arts (EA)</strong>, where she served as a <strong>Production Designer</strong>, bringing digital assets to life for a global audience and honing her ability to deliver high-quality work at scale.
                </p>

                <p class="mb-6 leading-relaxed text-lg">
                    Ana’s expertise represents a <strong>total creative package</strong>, spanning web design, UI/UX, and branding to audiovisual fields including <strong>photography, videography, and motion graphics</strong>. Often enhanced by <strong>AI-powered tools</strong>, her work is driven by a passion for crafting visual content with meaningful impact.
                </p>

                <p class="mb-6 leading-relaxed text-lg">
                    Beyond her design work, Ana Maria is an accomplished <strong>Music Producer and Singer-Songwriter</strong>. She writes and produces her own music—a creative practice that sharpens her intuition for <strong>rhythm and flow</strong>—qualities she brings to every digital product she builds. She blends creativity, technology, and strategy to design experiences that are not only beautiful but also <strong>intuitive and human</strong>.
                </p>
                <div class="flex gap-4">
                    <a href="https://res.cloudinary.com/dqbxkmkph/image/upload/v1759880005/Resume_Ana_Maria_Posada_-2025_mohnwb.pdf"class="secondary-btn">CHECK MY RESUME</a>
                    <a href="https://calendar.app.google/Ltp15FQaPxhoeaZS9" class="primary-btn">LET'S WORK TOGETHER</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
